I"
<p>Check which preempts are set on your distribution:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> <span class="nb">cat</span> /boot/config-4.15.0-50-generic | <span class="nb">grep </span>PREEMPT
</code></pre></div></div>
<ul>
  <li>CONFIG_PREEMPT</li>
  <li>CONFIG_PREEMPTIRQ_EVENTS</li>
  <li>CONFIG_HZ</li>
</ul>

<p>These options should be set (according to <a href="https://www.osadl.org/Real-time-Ethernet-UDP-worst-case-roun.qa-farm-rt-ethernet-udp-monitor.0.html">Real time ethernet</a>)</p>
<ul>
  <li>CONFIG_RCU_BOOST=y</li>
  <li>CONFIG_RCU_BOOST_PRIO=99</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.advenage.com/topics/linux-timer-interrupt-frequency">How To determine Linux Kernel Timer Interrupt Frequency</a></p>

<p><a href="https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/linux-device-drivers/0596005903/ch10.html">Interupt handling</a>
<a href="https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_enterprise_linux/6/html/performance_tuning_guide/index">Red hat performance tuning</a></p>

